                    "description": "Working on the development of Green bi-propellant rocket engines for in-space applications. \n\u25ba Responsible for the design, assembly, qualification, and acceptance testing of a 1N additively manufactured green bi-propellant thruster. Developed two different variants: one for cubesat applications and one for small satellite applications.\n\u25ba Designed several research thruster prototypes in the 1N-20N class range using Solidworks and performed design and thermal/performance analysis of research thrusters using Matlab.\n\u25ba Developed two automated test set ups for the development and acceptance testing of 1N class bi-propellant rocket engines. Was responsible for the full development and design including the electronics, mechanical hardware (which included vacuum chambers) and the software, which was programmed using Labview RT and FPGA programming. Additionally was responsible for processing and analysing the data obtained with the test set-up using Matlab programming.\n\u25ba Involved in the pre-launch preparation and in-orbit comissioning of propulsion systems.\n\u25ba Was involved in several hardware in the loop tests to test firing strategies and compatibility of satellite propulsion systems in combination with customer hardware. Was responsible for preparing and executing the tests.",
